&lt;li&gt;5+ years of RF engineering experience with a B.S. degree, or 3+ years with an M.S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of fundamental RF concepts: circuit analysis, noise figure, linearity, gain, radio architecture, and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience designing, building, and testing RF hardware at microwave and/or millimeter-wave frequencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in RF/EM simulation tools (ADS, HFSS, Cadence, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in schematic capture and multilayer PCB layout (Altium preferred).

